reviewText:
I loved this one. A perfect example of what a Hidden Objects game should be, in my opinion:
decent graphics;
LOTS of HO scenes;
achievements that are actually achievable (without the need of a guide to find where the heck is Collectibles #384" and without having to play the entire game twice);
original HO mechanics for those objects you have to perform an additional action on before finding them;
a decent variety of minigames.It's not the BEST HO game available - the story is banal and dulland here and there it shows that it's not really made by Artifex Mundi - but it's really good and I had fun playing it. I recommend it."
